comments: Hunter (ATL) places his forearm to Claxton's (BKN) side as they come together and marginal body contact occurs  as Claxton rolls to the basket.
Hunter (ATL) establishes himself in Bridges' (BKN) path and is firming up when marginal contact occurs.
Johnson (BKN) places a hand on Young's (ATL) front which affects Young's SQBR during his drive.
Bridges (BKN) places his hands against Young's (ATL side and immediately slides his hands off at the start of his drive.
Capela (ATL) initiates contact with Claxton (BKN) that impedes his ability to pursue the rebound.
Claxton (BKN) establishes himself in Hunter's (ATL) path and absorbs the contact.
Young (ATL) contests Finney-Smith's (BKN) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Capela (ATL) briefly places his hand to Claxton's (BKN) side as they come together in the lane and slides his hand off as they pursue the loose ball.
Bridges (BKN) immediately removes his arm off Young's (ATL) side as he gathers the ball and marginal contact occurs contesting his driving shot attempt.
Johnson (BKN) and Murray (ATL) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Johnson (BKN) brings his hand to the side of the ball, and continues his dribble.
Young (ATL) makes contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Dinwiddie (BKN) during his driving shot attempt.
Claxton (BKN) jumps along Murray's (ATL) path and marginal body contact occurs during his driving shot attempt.

After communicating with the Replay Center, it was confirmed Bey (ATL) initiates contact with the rim, causing the rim to move out of its stationary position and subsequently causing the ball to bounce unnaturally on it during the shot attempt.
Finney-Smith (BKN) initiates contact with Bey's (ATL) wrist, which affects his put-back shot attempt.
Hunter (ATL) engages and disengages with Bridges (BKN) and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Dinwiddie (BKN) establishes himself in Hunter's (ATL) path and is firming up when marginal contact occurs to Hunter's side as he defends over the screen.
Hunter (ATL) initiates marginal contact to Bridges' (BKN) body contesting his layup attempt.
Young (ATL) places his forearm to Bridges' (BKN) side and releases away from the contact as he gathers into his step-back move at the end of his drive.
Young (ATL) commits a take foul on Dinwiddie (BKN).
Claxton (BKN) and Capela (ATL) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Coach Snyder is granted a timeout prior to any contact occurring to Murray (ATL) in transition.
Bogdanovic (ATL) engages with Finney-Smith (BKN) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Bogdanovic (ATL) releases away from the contact.
Smith Jr. (BKN) places his arm against Young's (ATL) side and marginal contact occurs during Young's drive.
Smith Jr. (BKN) legally contests Young's (ATL) jump shot attempt. and marginal lower body contact occurs with Young after the release.
Bridges (BKN) places his forearm to Hunter's (ATL) front at the end of his drive and marginal contact occurs as Bridges' releases into his jump shot attempt.
Bogdanovic (ATL) slightly extends his arms against Dinwiddie (BKN) as he sets the screen and marginal body contact occurs as they disengage.
From all available angles, Bridges (BKN) appears to make no hand contact to Young (ATL) when he swipes at the ball, and he clearly and conclusively does not make foot contact.

Smith Jr. (BKN) does not impede Young's (ATL) progress with his left hand before Young wipes his hand back. Smith Jr. then legally places a forearm to Young's side and releases him without extending or pushing him.
